creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Short Poetry Collection 146 by Various.
Read in English by Newgatenovelist; Ian King; Leonard Wilson; SciE; Shakira Searle; Craig Campbell; Algy Pug; Bruce Kachuk; Winston Tharp; DannyHauger; Son of the Exiles; David Bushhouse; Sarah Sellari
This collection of 29 poems, read by LibriVox volunteers for July 2015, includes: An Aeolian Harp, by Michael Field After Death, by Christina Rossetti All at Sea, by Frederick Moxon Amor Vitae, by Archibald Lampman At Night, by Amy Lowell Cornelius Agrippa's Epitaph, by Unknown Coming Home, by Augusta Webster The Dong with a Luminous Nose, by Edward Lear Hymne to God my God, in my sicknesse, by John Donne I Am The Reaper, by William Ernest Henley Is My Team Ploughing, by A. E. Housman July Midnight, by Amy Lowell London Snow, by Robert Bridges Love and Life, by John Wilmot A Lover, by Amy Lowell Love’s Philosophy, by Percy Bysshe Shelley Midnight, by Archibald Lampman Night on the Prairies, by Walt Whitman O, Gather Me The Rose, by William Ernest Henley Outgrown, by Julia Caroline Dorr Over the Wall, by Julia Caroline Dorr On the Painting of the Sistine Chapel, by Michelangelo Buonarroti Paul’s Wife, by Robert Frost The Riders in the Stand, by Andrew Barton "Banjo" Paterson Two Loves, by Lord Alfred Douglas The Unlovely, by James Russell Lowell Verses, by Laurence Hope Where Forlorn Sunsets Flare and Fade, by William Ernest Henley You Remain, by Arthur Symons
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
